description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 - Project Support Manager, UK NEQAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time- 37.5 hours per week, 12 Month Fixed Term&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UK NEQAS Haematology and Blood Transfusion delivers a diverse and extensive programme of EQA services to 1400 participating laboratories in the UK and worldwide, which is set to develop in the near future to meet the requirements of service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and versatile individual to support the project management of the upcoming site relocation of the unit. The post holder will report to the Business and Finance Manager, providing a coordinated day to day support for project activities including project planning, monitoring and management, change control, risk and issue monitoring and project reporting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also support other administrative related projects within the unit aimed at improving workflow and efficiency within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would expect you to have a degree level qualification, knowledge of project management approaches and experience of working in a project environment. You must have excellent communication skills, be a great team player and have excellent organisational skills to handle changing priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UK NEQAS Haematology and Blood Transfusion is operated by the West Herts Hospitals NHS Trust and the post is a 12-month fixed term NHS appointment based at Watford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nazia Hussain&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Nazia.Hussain16@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01923 217878&lt;/p&gt;
